{
  "texts": [
    "These features can vary from simple ones, such as word or essay length, to complex features like readability and coherence.",
    "Uto et al. (2020) presented several handcrafted features, including length-based, syntactic, word-based, readability, semantic, argumentation and prompt-relevant features.",
    "These features represent several feature examples, for instance, length-based features represent number of characters, words, sentences, and punctuation.",
    "Hoblos (2020) employed a semantic feature representation approach to enhance the essay representation by incorporating word meaning and sense.",
    "Besides using contentbased essay representation, syntactic feature representation mechanisms like part-of-speech (POS) embedding has been utilized to build generalizable AES models (Ridley et al. 2020 (Ridley et al., 2021;; Jin et al. 2018)."
  ]
}